{
  "name": "Debilitate: Rakunda",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/control/fear-fright-white.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you would make an attack or cast a Ninjutsu or Genjutsu that affects a hostile creature, you can expend a Superiority Die to weaken a creature's defensive capabilities.</p><p>One creature who would fail your Jutsu's saving throw takes additional damage equal to twice your Proficiency Bonus, the next time they take damage before the end of the current turn.</p><p>If your attack does not trigger a saving throw then affected creatures must make a Charisma Saving throw vs your Ninjutsu or Genjutsu save DC (Your choice.)</p><p>If this maneuver is used by your Void soul, or while you are benefiting from Tricksters Soul Binding, the additional damage increases by 4 times your Superiority Die result.</p><p></p>",
